msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/name"
msgid "Tears and Sweat"
msgstr "Sudor y lágrimas"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/name_big"
msgid "Tears and Sweat"
msgstr "Sudor y lágrimas"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/date"
msgid "May 13th, 1940 · Town of Korbeek-Dijle, Belgium"
msgstr "13 de mayo de 1940 · Localidad de Korbeek-Dijle, Bélgica"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/place"
msgid "1st Infantry Division, North Staffordshire Regiment"
msgstr "1.ª División de Infantería, Regimiento de North Staffordshire"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/story"
msgid ""
"The phony war has erupted into Blitzkrieg! The Germans invade the "
"Netherlands and Belgium on May 10th. What the Germans call “Fall Gelb” is "
"underway.\n"
"\n"
"You have been ordered north with your unit to reinforce the Dyle line.\n"
"\n"
"Your part of the line is at a bridge, not far from Louvain. The Germans will "
"definitely want to use this bridge to get to Brussels, so this is a key "
"position in the Dyle line."
msgstr ""
"La guerra de mentira ha estallado en Blitzkrieg. Los alemanes invaden los "
"Países Bajos y Bélgica el 10 de mayo. Lo que los alemanes llaman “Fall Gelb” "
"está en marcha.\n"
"\n"
"Has recibido la orden de dirigirte hacia el norte con tu unidad para "
"reforzar la línea Dyle.\n"
"\n"
"Tu parte de la línea está en un puente, no lejos de Lovaina. Los alemanes "
"sin duda querrán usar este puente para llegar a Bruselas, así que es una "
"posición clave en la línea."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/outro_completed"
msgid ""
"We have shown them what to expect from the British Expeditionary force. We "
"might be retreating from the battle today, but we bought ourselves and our "
"allies some more time."
msgstr ""
"Les hemos mostrado lo que pueden esperar de la Fuerza Expedicionaria "
"Británica. Puede que hoy nos hayamos retirado de la batalla, pero hemos "
"ganado algo más de tiempo para nosotros y nuestros aliados."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/outro_failed"
msgid ""
"That is rather unfortunate, we should have held the line here. Because we "
"haven’t stopped this brutal attack, Jerry can now continue his drive into "
"Belgium and toward France, unfortunately."
msgstr ""
"Es una pena, deberíamos haber mantenido la línea aquí. Como no hemos "
"detenido este brutal ataque, Jerry ahora puede continuar su avance hacia "
"Bélgica y Francia, por desgracia."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/doc_allround_01"
msgid ""
"The 6-inch howitzer has arrived. We got only one chance, don’t screw this up!"
msgstr ""
"El obús de 6 pulgadas ha llegado. Solo tenemos una oportunidad, ¡no la eches "
"a perder!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/doc_allround_02"
msgid ""
"Jerry has spotted our gun! They will open fire in no time, change the "
"position of the bloody howitzer, quickly!"
msgstr ""
"¡Jerry ha visto vuestra arma! Van a abrir fuego en cualquier momento, "
"cambien la posición del maldito obús, ¡rápido!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/doc_allround_03"
msgid "Nice shot, one gun down. Two left!"
msgstr "Buen tiro, un arma menos. ¡Quedan dos!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/doc_allround_04"
msgid "Brillant, two guns down. One left!"
msgstr "Genial, dos pistolas menos. ¡Queda una!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/doc_allround_05"
msgid "The enemy artillery is now silent, great job!"
msgstr "La artillería enemiga ahora está en silencio, ¡buen trabajo!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/doc_allround_06"
msgid ""
"Bloody hell, we just lost our howitzer! I don’t know how but you have to "
"find an alternative way to deal with the German artillery."
msgstr ""
"¡Maldita sea, acabamos de perder nuestro obús! No sé cómo, pero tienes que "
"encontrar una forma alternativa de lidiar con la artillería alemana."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/doc_defensive_01"
msgid ""
"The anti-air Vickers has arrived. We got only one chance, don’t screw this "
"up!"
msgstr ""
"El Vickers antiaéreo ha llegado. Solo tenemos una oportunidad, ¡no la eches "
"a perder!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/doc_defensive_02"
msgid ""
"The pilot has spotted our anti-air vehicle! Change its position, quickly!"
msgstr ""
"¡El piloto ha visto nuestro vehículo antiaéreo! ¡Cambia su posición, rápido!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/doc_defensive_03"
msgid "Nice shot, this plane is down."
msgstr "Buen tiro, este avión ha caído."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/doc_defensive_04"
msgid ""
"Watch out, there comes another one! It’s engaging your anti-air vehicle!"
msgstr "¡Cuidado! ¡Ahí viene otro! ¡Está atacando tu vehículo antiaéreo!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/doc_defensive_05"
msgid ""
"Brilliant shot but there is a third plane approaching your location, deal "
"with it!"
msgstr ""
"¡Excelente disparo, pero hay un tercer avión acercándose a tu posición, "
"ocúpate de él!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/doc_defensive_06"
msgid "I think it was the last of ‘em. Good job."
msgstr "Creo que era el último. Buen trabajo."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/doc_defensive_07"
msgid ""
"Blimey, we just lost our anti-air vehicle! I don’t know how but you have to "
"find an alternative way to deal with the Luftwaffe."
msgstr ""
"¡Caramba, acabamos de perder nuestro vehículo antiaéreo! No sé cómo, pero "
"tienes que encontrar una forma alternativa de lidiar con la Luftwaffe."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/doc_irregular_01"
msgid ""
"The artillery observer has arrived. Don’t let Jerry spot him. We got only "
"one chance, make this a good one!"
msgstr ""
"El observador de artillería ha llegado. No dejes que Jerry lo vea. Solo "
"tenemos una oportunidad, ¡aprovechala bien!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/doc_irregular_02"
msgid "Watch out, the observer has been spotted!"
msgstr "¡Cuidado, han visto al observador!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/doc_irregular_03"
msgid "Great, this anti-air gun will not bother us anymore!"
msgstr "¡Genial, este cañón antiaéreo ya no nos molestará más!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/doc_irregular_04"
msgid "Brilliant, the AT gun is destroyed."
msgstr "Genial, el cañón antitanque ha sido destruido."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/doc_irregular_05"
msgid "Excellent, the guns have been destroyed."
msgstr "Excelente, las armas han sido destruidas."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/doc_irregular_06"
msgid ""
"Dammit, the observer has been killed! Find another way to destroy the "
"emplacements!"
msgstr ""
"¡Maldita sea, han matado al observador! ¡Encuentra otra forma de destruir "
"las posiciones!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/doc_offensive_01"
msgid "Matilda has arrived. We got only one chance, don’t screw this up!"
msgstr ""
"El Matilda ha llegado. Solo tenemos una oportunidad, ¡no la eches a perder!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/doc_offensive_02"
msgid "The Panzers have spotted our tank, you have to deal with ‘em, quickly!"
msgstr ""
"Los Panzers han visto nuestro tanque, ¡tienes que ocuparte de ellos, rápido!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/doc_offensive_03"
msgid "Brilliant, one Panzer down, destroy the second one!"
msgstr "¡Genial, un Panzer menos, destruye el segundo!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/doc_offensive_04"
msgid "Great job, both tanks have been destroyed!"
msgstr "¡Buen trabajo, los dos tanques han sido destruidos!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/doc_offensive_05"
msgid ""
"Blimey, we lost our tank! I hope you still have some 2-pounders at your "
"disposal."
msgstr ""
"¡Diablos, hemos perdido nuestro tanque! Espero que aún tengas algunos "
"cañones de dos libras a tu disposición."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/heavy_wounded_died"
msgid ""
"He’s gone. Could’ve saved him… That medic’s yours now. Do better next time."
msgstr ""
"Ha muerto. Podrías haberlo salvado... Ese médico ahora es tuyo. Hazlo mejor "
"la próxima vez."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/heavy_wounded_rescued"
msgid ""
"Alright, he’ll make it. Bet this lad won’t forget your help for the rest of "
"his life."
msgstr ""
"Muy bien, lo conseguirá. Apuesto a que este chico no olvidará tu ayuda en "
"toda su vida."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/heavy_wounded_start"
msgid "Williams, I need one more hand on this one, quick!"
msgstr "Williams, necesito otra mano con esto, ¡rápido!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/cutscene/intro_01"
msgid ""
"…Honestly, I’m sick of marching and digging trenches. And this heat… I "
"swear, mate, it’s even worse than Kenya, back when I was on assignment. At "
"least I had better company there. A lovely Mathilda…"
msgstr ""
"Sinceramente, estoy harto de marchar y cavar trincheras. Y este calor... Te "
"lo juro, amigo, es incluso peor que en Kenia, cuando estuve allí de misión. "
"Al menos allí tenía mejor compañía. Una encantadora Mathilda..."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/cutscene/intro_02"
msgid ""
"Look at that, they even named that clanking monster in her honour. I’ve "
"never told you about that trip, have I?"
msgstr ""
"Mira, incluso le pusieron ese nombre al monstruo chirriante en tu honor. "
"Nunca te he contado nada de ese viaje, ¿verdad?"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/cutscene/intro_03"
msgid ""
"For Christ’s sake, Williams. Can you shut it for once? We’re all bloody sick "
"of your stories."
msgstr ""
"Por el amor de Dios, Williams. ¿Puedes callarte por una vez? Todos estamos "
"hartos de tus historias."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/cutscene/intro_04"
msgid ""
"Take it easy, Stu. I’m just trying to lift your spirits. You’re looking far "
"too knackered for our little continental adventure. What’s wrong, ja? Scared "
"of the Jerries?"
msgstr ""
"Tranquilo, Stu. Solo intento animarte. Pareces demasiado agotado para "
"nuestra pequeña aventura continental. ¿Qué pasa, ja? ¿Te dan miedo los "
"alemanes?"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/cutscene/intro_05"
msgid ""
"Well spotted, genius. You are not even slightly bothered that the bloody "
"Luftwaffe doesn’t let us sleep more than an hour a night? We’re all "
"knackered, alright?"
msgstr ""
"Bien visto, genio. ¿No te molesta ni un poco que la maldita Luftwaffe no nos "
"deje dormir más de una hora por noche? Estamos todos agotados, ¿vale?"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/cutscene/intro_06"
msgid "Shh, keep it down. The Captain seems really stressed today."
msgstr "Shh, no hables tan alto. El capitán parece muy estresado hoy."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/cutscene/intro_07"
msgid ""
"We’re alright for now. They’ve decided to send another company forward. "
"We’re not going with this column. We need to double-check for potential gaps "
"in our lines. Given the news, we might not be here much longer… But let’s "
"prepare for the worst."
msgstr ""
"Por ahora estamos bien. Han decidido enviar a otra compañía al frente. No "
"vamos a ir con esta columna. Tenemos que volver a comprobar si hay posibles "
"brechas en nuestras líneas. Dadas las noticias, puede que no estemos aquí "
"mucho más tiempo... Pero preparémonos para lo peor."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/cutscene/intro_10"
msgid ""
"And for God’s sake, get that bloody 2-pounder out of the middle of the path "
"already."
msgstr ""
"Y, por el amor de Dios, quita ya esa maldita piedra de dos kilos del medio "
"del camino."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/cutscene/intro_08"
msgid ""
"We’re not? I thought the frontline was going to stay static again. Just like "
"last month. And the month before that. And half a bloody year ago... You "
"know, Sir."
msgstr ""
"¿No? Pensaba que el frente iba a permanecer estático otra vez. Igual que el "
"mes pasado. Y el mes anterior. Y hace medio año... Ya tú sabes, señor."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/cutscene/intro_09"
msgid ""
"I reckon our luck has left us for now. It’s... it’s a bloody mess out there. "
"But we’ll be fine. We will. Just… Just do your thing, gentlemen."
msgstr ""
"Creo que por ahora la suerte nos ha abandonado. Es... es un auténtico caos "
"ahí fuera. Pero estaremos bien. Lo estaremos. Solo... Solo haced lo que "
"tenéis que hacer, caballeros."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/medic_died_01"
msgid "Hawkins! Christ, we lost one of our medics!"
msgstr "¡Hawkins! ¡Dios mío, hemos perdido a uno de nuestros médicos!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/medic_died_02"
msgid "Williams! What the hell are you doing?! That medic is a goner!"
msgstr "¡Williams! ¡¿Qué demonios estás haciendo?! ¡Ese médico está perdido!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/medic_died_03"
msgid "Bloody hell, Crosby is down! We need to fall back, now!"
msgstr ""
"¡Maldita sea, Crosby está herido! ¡Tenemos que retirarnos, ahora mismo!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part01_01"
msgid "Shit… They’re just gone… One strike and that’s it…"
msgstr "Mierda... Se han ido... Un golpe y ya está..."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part01_02"
msgid ""
"I need you to focus, men. There must be someone who has managed to find "
"cover. I know that sending a small group like yours is risky but the "
"Luftwaffe leaves me no choice."
msgstr ""
"Necesito que os concentréis, muchachos. Tiene que haber alguien que haya "
"conseguido ponerse a cubierto. Sé que enviar a un grupo pequeño como el "
"vuestro es arriesgado, pero la Luftwaffe no me deja otra opción."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part01_03"
msgid ""
"Lieutenant Williams, your objective is to secure the area in case Jerry "
"decides to scavenge the wrecks. No way those planes knew the convoy’s "
"location without someone guiding ‘em from the ground. There should be some "
"scout rats, for sure."
msgstr ""
"Teniente Williams, tu objetivo es asegurar la zona por si Jerry decide "
"saquear los restos. Es imposible que esos aviones supieran la ubicación del "
"convoy sin que alguien los guiara desde tierra. Seguro que hay algunas ratas "
"exploradoras."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part01_04"
msgid ""
"Corporal Crosby, you’re in charge of the medical team. Search for survivors "
"and provide assistance. Williams, cover the medics at all costs. Report me "
"when you’re ready for evacuation and I’ll send a lorry for the wounded. I "
"can’t do it right now, the skies are too hot. Out."
msgstr ""
"Cabo Crosby, tú estás a cargo del equipo médico. Busca supervivientes y "
"presta asistencia. Williams, cubre a los médicos a toda costa. Avísame "
"cuando estéis listos para la evacuación y enviaré un camión para los "
"heridos. Ahora mismo no puedo hacerlo, el cielo está demasiado caliente. "
"Cambio y corto."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part01_05"
msgid ""
"Gosh… No one warned about the smell… Look at ‘em… They’re all… Burnt… I feel "
"so sick."
msgstr ""
"Vaya... Nadie me advirtió sobre el olor... Míralos... Están todos... "
"Quemados... Me siento muy mal."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part01_06"
msgid ""
"It’ll be fine, alright? Pull yourself together. Keep an eye out for cover in "
"case Jerry returns."
msgstr ""
"Todo irá bien, ¿de acuerdo? Recompónte. Mantente alerta por si Jerry regresa."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part01_07"
msgid "Fuck! I just… I just touched his fucking skin and…"
msgstr "¡Joder! Acabo de... Acabo de tocar tu maldita piel y..."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part01_08"
msgid ""
"Hey, take it easy mate. Think of something good. You'll be so bloody telling "
"me about that Matilda girl of yours when we get out of here."
msgstr ""
"Oye, tranquilo, amigo. Piensa en algo bueno. Me contarás todo sobre esa "
"chica tuya, Matilda, cuando salgamos de aquí."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part01_09"
msgid "We’ve got company from the north!"
msgstr "¡Tenemos compañía del norte!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part01_10"
msgid "Jerry coming from the southeast!"
msgstr "¡Jerry viene del sureste!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part01_11"
msgid "Williams, we heard gunfire. What’s going on? Over."
msgstr "Williams, hemos oído disparos. ¿Qué está pasando? Cambio."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part01_12"
msgid ""
"Light German infantry approaching from multiple directions. We’ve found "
"wounded, Crosby and his team are treating ‘em. Over."
msgstr ""
"Infantería alemana ligera acercándose desde múltiples direcciones. Hemos "
"encontrado heridos, Crosby y su equipo los están atendiendo. Cambio."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part01_13"
msgid "Copy that, sending help to you. Out."
msgstr "Entendido, enviando ayuda. Cambio y corto."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part01_14"
msgid "Enemy vehicle coming from the north, take it down!"
msgstr "Vehículo enemigo procedente del norte, ¡derríbalos!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part01_15"
msgid "Enemy aircraft! Everyone, get the hell down!"
msgstr "¡Aviones enemigos! ¡Todos al suelo!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part01_16"
msgid ""
"Man… That was a recon plane… Means the whole bloody German army knows we’re "
"here. Crosby, get it done! Quickly!"
msgstr ""
"Tío... Era un avión de reconocimiento... Eso significa que todo el maldito "
"ejército alemán sabe que estamos aquí. ¡Crosby, hazlo! ¡Rápido!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part01_17"
msgid "We’re good to go. Williams, call it in!"
msgstr "Estamos listos. ¡Williams, avisa!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part01_18"
msgid ""
"Captain, this is Williams. We’re ready for an evacuation. The skies are "
"clear at the moment, over."
msgstr ""
"Capitán, aquí Williams. Estamos listos para la evacuación. El cielo está "
"despejado en este momento, cambio."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part01_19"
msgid ""
"Understood, Lieutenant. Lorry’s on the way, it’s three minutes away. Good "
"work, lads. Out."
msgstr ""
"Entendido, teniente. El camión está en camino, llegará en tres minutos. Buen "
"trabajo, muchachos. Corto."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part01_21"
msgid "Lorry is ready! Crosby, get the wounded into it, now!"
msgstr "¡El camión está listo! Crosby, mete a los heridos dentro, ¡ya!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part01_22"
msgid "Everyone in, let’s get the hell out of here!"
msgstr "¡Todos dentro, salgamos pitando de aquí!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part01_23"
msgid "We’ll follow behind. Get ‘em to safety. See you on the other side."
msgstr "Te seguiremos. Ponlos a salvo. Nos vemos al otro lado."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part01_progress_02"
msgid "Just need a bit more time. Keep us covered."
msgstr "Solo necesitamos un poco más de tiempo. Mantenednos informados."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part01_ammo_out"
msgid ""
"I’m out of ammo! Think I’ve seen an ammunition crate on the road, let’s have "
"a peek."
msgstr ""
"¡Me he quedado sin munición! Creo que he visto una caja de municiones en la "
"carretera, vamos a echar un vistazo."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part02_01"
msgid ""
"Lads, listen up! The Huns are even closer to the Dyle River than we thought. "
"We still have some time to prepare the defense. Use it to reinforce our "
"positions."
msgstr ""
"¡Chicos, escuchad! Los hunos están aún más cerca del río Dyle de lo que "
"pensábamos. Todavía tenemos algo de tiempo para preparar la defensa. "
"Aprovechadlo para reforzar nuestras posiciones."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part02_02"
msgid "Here they are, pushing our central positions! Hold your ground!"
msgstr ""
"¡Ahí están, presionando nuestras posiciones centrales! ¡Mantén tu posición!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part02_03"
msgid ""
"We weren’t trained for this kind of defence! Why are they hammering one spot "
"instead of pushing along the whole frontline?"
msgstr ""
"¡No nos han entrenado para este tipo de defensa! ¿Por qué atacan un solo "
"punto en lugar de avanzar por todo el frente?"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part02_04"
msgid ""
"Probably their famous tactics they are using right now. One hard push in a "
"vulnerable direction. Watch your less-protected areas!"
msgstr ""
"Probablemente sea la famosa táctica que están utilizando ahora mismo. Un "
"fuerte empujón en una dirección vulnerable. ¡Cuidado con las zonas menos "
"protegidas!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part02_05"
msgid ""
"I’ve managed to get through to HQ. They’re willing to send reinforcements, "
"but only to cover our losses. Resources are very tight, so don’t expect "
"anything extra."
msgstr ""
"He conseguido contactar con el cuartel general. Están dispuestos a enviar "
"refuerzos, pero solo para cubrir nuestras bajas. Los recursos son muy "
"escasos, así que no esperes nada más."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part02_06"
msgid ""
"Sir, did they tell you the latest information on the frontline? What’s "
"happening?"
msgstr ""
"Señor, ¿te han contado las últimas noticias del frente? ¿Qué está pasando?"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part02_07"
msgid ""
"From what I can tell… We’re exceeding the expectations so far. Keep it that "
"way."
msgstr ""
"Por lo que puedo ver... Hasta ahora estamos superando las expectativas. "
"Seguid así."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part02_08"
msgid "We slowed ‘em down, lads! Now destroy the remaining enemy vehicles!"
msgstr ""
"¡Los hemos frenado, muchachos! ¡Ahora destruyan los vehículos enemigos "
"restantes!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part03_01"
msgid ""
"Jerry has taken control of our northern flank! I am sending our last "
"reserves to re-capture these positions before our whole entire defense "
"falls. Lieutenant Williams, I need you to provide support for their counter-"
"attack."
msgstr ""
"¡Jerry ha tomado el control de nuestro flanco norte! Voy a enviar nuestras "
"últimas reservas para recuperar estas posiciones antes de que toda nuestra "
"defensa caiga. Teniente Williams, necesito que prestes apoyo a su "
"contraataque."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part03_02_allround"
msgid ""
"The enemy has brought in their heavy guns! My forces will not be able to "
"counter attack while the howitzers are still operational. We have to deal "
"with ‘em first."
msgstr ""
"¡El enemigo ha traído sus armas pesadas! Mis fuerzas no podrán contraatacar "
"mientras los obuses sigan operativos. Tenemos que ocuparnos de ellos primero."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part03_02_defensive"
msgid ""
"There is a Jerry plane hanging about! It makes no sense to attack while "
"Jerry has close air support. My forces have no anti-air equipment, so you "
"guys have to deal with it on your own."
msgstr ""
"¡Hay un avión alemán merodeando! No tiene sentido atacar mientras los "
"alemanes tengan apoyo aéreo cercano. Mis fuerzas no tienen equipo antiaéreo, "
"así que tendréis que encargaros vosotros mismos."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part03_02_irregular"
msgid ""
"The enemy has brought in their emplacements! The AT and AA guns must be "
"destroyed first. My forces will not be able to counter attack while the guns "
"are still operational. We have to deal with those first."
msgstr ""
"¡El enemigo ha traído sus emplazamientos! Hay que destruir primero los "
"cañones antitanque y antiaéreos. Mis fuerzas no podrán contraatacar mientras "
"los cañones sigan operativos. Tenemos que ocuparnos de ellos primero."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part03_02_offensive"
msgid ""
"The enemy has brought in their tanks! These tanks must be destroyed first. "
"My forces have no anti-tank weapons, so you guys have to deal with ‘em on "
"your own."
msgstr ""
"¡El enemigo ha traído sus tanques! Hay que destruirlos primero. Mis fuerzas "
"no tienen armas antitanque, así que tendréis que encargaros de ellos "
"vosotros mismos."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part03_03"
msgid ""
"My lads are ready to advance to the German positions. Give me a signal once "
"you’re ready."
msgstr ""
"Mis muchachos están listos para avanzar hacia las posiciones alemanas. Dame "
"una señal cuando estés listo."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part03_03_allround"
msgid ""
"We still have a royal ace up our sleeve, though. I am granting you access to "
"a 6-inch howitzer for counter artillery combat. We only have one, so please "
"be careful with this old lady. The Jerries will most likely open fire in "
"response after a single shot, that’s why you have to put the Morris carrier "
"to good use. Change your position after every shot."
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, todavía tenemos un as en la manga. Te concedo acceso a un obús "
"de 15 cm para el combate de artillería antiaérea. Solo tenemos uno, así que "
"ten cuidado con esta vieja dama. Es muy probable que los alemanes respondan "
"abriendo fuego tras un solo disparo, por lo que debes hacer buen uso del "
"transporte Morris. Cambia de posición después de cada disparo."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part03_03_defensive"
msgid ""
"We still have a royal ace up our sleeve, though. I am granting you access to "
"an ack-ack tank to take this bloody plane down. We only have one, so please "
"be careful with this lad. The pilot will most likely try to take this "
"vehicle down once he spots it, so be careful and change your position as "
"often as you can."
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, todavía tenemos un as en la manga. Te concedo acceso a un "
"tanque antiaéreo para derribar ese maldito avión. Solo tenemos uno, así que "
"ten cuidado con él. Es muy probable que el piloto intente derribar este "
"vehículo en cuanto lo vea, así que ten cuidado y cambia de posición tan a "
"menudo como puedas."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part03_03_irregular"
msgid ""
"We still have a royal ace up our sleeve, though. I am granting you access to "
"an artillery observer to provide exact coordinates to our artillery. Make "
"the ground tremble under their feet. We only have one specialist, so make "
"sure Jerry does not spot him."
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, todavía tenemos un as en la manga. Te concedo acceso a un "
"observador de artillería para que proporcione las coordenadas exactas a "
"nuestra artillería. Haz que la tierra tiemble bajo sus pies. Solo tenemos un "
"especialista, así que asegúrate de que Jerry no lo vea."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part03_03_offensive"
msgid ""
"We still have a royal ace up our sleeve, though. I am granting you access to "
"a Matilda II tank which is capable of taking out both Panzers. We only have "
"one, so please be careful with this young lady. However, keep your distance "
"from the Jerries, we don’t know how they might respond."
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, todavía tenemos un as en la manga. Te concedo acceso a un "
"tanque Matilda II, capaz de destruir ambos Panzers. Solo tenemos uno, así "
"que ten cuidado con esta señorita. No obstante, mantén la distancia con los "
"alemanes, no sabemos cómo podrían reaccionar."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part03_04"
msgid "Alright lads, move, move!"
msgstr "¡Muy bien, muchachos, moveos, moveos!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part03_05"
msgid "The northern flank is under our control again. Brilliant job, everyone!"
msgstr ""
"El flanco norte vuelve a estar bajo nuestro control. ¡Buen trabajo a todos!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part03_06"
msgid "Seems like we stopped their advance…"
msgstr "Parece que hemos detenido su avance..."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/part03_07"
msgid "I reckon we did… So, what’s the next step?"
msgstr "Creo que sí... Entonces, ¿cuál es el siguiente paso?"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/pl_swimming"
msgid ""
"Blimey, the water’s lovely and warm today. Now if only we could get a couple "
"of girls from the village to join us, that’d be just perfect."
msgstr ""
"Caramba, hoy el agua está estupenda y calentita. Ahora, si pudiéramos "
"conseguir que un par de chicas del pueblo se unieran a nosotros, sería "
"perfecto."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/preparation_01"
msgid ""
"I wasn’t much for saying thank you back then. Just thought none of us would "
"make it out alive anyway."
msgstr ""
"En aquel entonces no solía dar las gracias. Simplemente pensaba que ninguno "
"de nosotros saldría vivo de allí."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/preparation_02"
msgid ""
"Don’t mention. And sorry for being a pain in the ass with those stories I’ve "
"told a hundred times. Just trying to keep your spirits up."
msgstr ""
"No te preocupes. Y perdona por ser tan pesado con esas historias que ya he "
"contado cientos de veces. Solo intento animarte."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/preparation_03"
msgid "Aye, no worries, mate."
msgstr "Sí, no te preocupes, amigo."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/preparation_04"
msgid "So… You mentioned Kenya, if I recall?"
msgstr "Entonces... ¿Has mencionado Kenia, si no recuerdo mal?"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/preparation_05"
msgid ""
"Oh yeah. You know what my uncle told me before I went? Said, “It’s like "
"India, only with golf, lions, and less…” You know what they say about it… "
"Bloody romantic, innit?"
msgstr ""
"Ah, sí. ¿Sabes lo que me dijo mi tío antes de irme? Me dijo: «Es como la "
"India, solo que con golf, leones y menos...». Ya sabes lo que se dice... Muy "
"romántico, ¿no?"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/preparation_06"
msgid "Oh, right… Here we go again…"
msgstr "Ah, claro... Aquí vamos otra vez..."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/preparation_07"
msgid ""
"He wasn’t joking. The whole family said the same thing: “Don’t come back "
"without a lion’s head, or you’re just a tourist in uniform.” To them, no "
"lion means no courage. And when you're the youngest son with no title and no "
"estate… Well, there aren’t many ways to prove yourself."
msgstr ""
"No estaba bromeando. Toda la familia dijo lo mismo: «No vuelvas sin una "
"cabeza de león, o no serás más que un turista con uniforme». Para ellos, no "
"tener un león significa no tener valor. Y cuando eres el hijo menor, sin "
"título ni patrimonio... Bueno, no hay muchas formas de demostrar tu valía."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/preparation_08"
msgid "So… did you actually get one?"
msgstr "Entonces... ¿te compraste uno?"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/preparation_09"
msgid ""
"Sort of. They assigned me a “gun bearer”. Local lad about my age. Poor "
"bloke’s job was to carry my kit around. Felt bloody strange… Like some "
"medieval knight with a squire behind me. Except he was doing it to feed "
"three kids."
msgstr ""
"Más o menos. Me asignaron un «portador de armas». Un chico de la zona, más o "
"menos de mi edad. El pobre tenía que llevar mi equipo. Me resultaba muy "
"extraño... Era como un caballero medieval con un escudero detrás. Excepto "
"que él lo hacía para alimentar a tres hijos."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/preparation_10"
msgid ""
"Didn’t know His Majesty Lord Williams felt so kindly toward us dirty "
"peasants."
msgstr ""
"No sabía que Su Majestad Lord Williams sentía tanta simpatía por nosotros, "
"los sucios campesinos."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/preparation_11"
msgid ""
"He barely did any “gun bearing”, to be fair. Carried my bags to the pub on "
"day one, and that was about it. After that, he was more like a guide. We "
"drank Pombe most of the time. That’s the local stuff. Made from sorghum and "
"bananas. It was good after three pints, though."
msgstr ""
"Para ser justos, apenas hizo nada. El primer día llevó mis maletas al pub, y "
"eso fue todo. Después de eso, fue más bien como un guía. Bebimos Pombe la "
"mayor parte del tiempo. Es la bebida local. Está hecha de sorgo y plátanos. "
"Sin embargo, después de tres pintas estaba buena."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/preparation_12"
msgid "Sounds like you really went native."
msgstr "Parece que realmente te has integrado."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/preparation_13"
msgid ""
"Too right. It’s much better than listening to my fellow Britons moaning all "
"day “Locals lack discipline,” “I miss proper football,” “Where’s the bloody "
"gin…” All that, while downing G&Ts like water. I was done with it. I just "
"wanted some peace."
msgstr ""
"Tienes toda la razón. Es mucho mejor que escuchar a mis compatriotas "
"británicos quejarse todo el día: «Los locales carecen de disciplina», «Echo "
"de menos el fútbol de verdad», «¿Dónde está la maldita ginebra?», etc., "
"mientras se beben gin-tonics como si fueran agua. Estaba harto. Solo quería "
"un poco de paz."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/preparation_14"
msgid "That sounds imperial enough. So… did you ever actually go after a lion?"
msgstr "Suena bastante imperial. Entonces... ¿alguna vez cazaste un león?"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/preparation_15"
msgid ""
"Course I didn’t. I’m not daft enough to leave a good pub for the bloody "
"savannah. Bought a lion’s head off some merchant before I sailed home. Gave "
"the gun bearer a solid tip and called it a day. What’s the point, really? "
"Chasing animals to prove something a bunch of dead men once wrote in a book?"
msgstr ""
"Por supuesto que no. No soy tan tonto como para dejar un buen pub por la "
"maldita sabana. Compré una cabeza de león a un comerciante antes de zarpar "
"hacia casa. Le di una buena propina al artillero y di por terminado el día. "
"¿Qué sentido tiene, en realidad? ¿Perseguir animales para demostrar algo que "
"un grupo de hombres muertos escribió una vez en un libro?"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/preparation_16"
msgid "Yeah… I get your point."
msgstr "Sí... Entiendo lo que quieres decir."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/preparation_17"
msgid ""
"So… Where was I? Ah, right. One night at that pub, me and my guide were "
"watching the sunset, sipping Pombe… You should’ve seen those sunsets, Stuey. "
"So bloody beautiful, I almost wrote a poem. For someone I’ll tell you about "
"in a second…"
msgstr ""
"Entonces... ¿Por dónde iba? Ah, sí. Una noche, en ese pub, mi guía y yo "
"estábamos contemplando la puesta de sol, bebiendo pombe... Tendrías que "
"haber visto esas puestas de sol, Stuey. Eran tan bonitas que casi escribo un "
"poema. Para alguien de quien te hablaré en un momento..."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/preparation_18"
msgid ""
"So we’re downing, I don’t know, our fifth drink, and out of nowhere, this "
"girl walks round the corner, right into the light of the sunset…"
msgstr ""
"Así que estamos tomando, no sé, vuestra quinta copa, y de repente, aparece "
"una chica doblando la esquina, justo a la luz del atardecer..."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/preparation_19"
msgid ""
"Lord Williams, sorry to interrupt your Shakespearean memoirs, but weren’t "
"you due at the commanders’ briefing two minutes ago? Where, unless I’m "
"mistaken, everyone’s already waiting?"
msgstr ""
"Lord Williams, siento interrumpir tus memorias sobre Shakespeare, pero ¿no "
"debías estar hace dos minutos en la reunión informativa de los comandantes? "
"Si no me equivoco, ¿todos están ya esperando?"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/preparation_20"
msgid "Oh, bloody hell! Sorry, sir! I’ll tell you about Matilda later."
msgstr "¡Maldita sea! ¡Lo siento, señor! Te hablaré de Matilda más tarde."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/preparation_21"
msgid "Aye. You bet."
msgstr "Sí, claro."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/cutscene/outro_01"
msgid ""
"Christ… Didn’t expect Jerry to have that many tanks. No one told us about "
"it. And even after this whole mess… We’re just leaving. I don’t know, it "
"feels like it was for nothing."
msgstr ""
"Dios... No esperaba que Jerry tuviera tantos tanques. Nadie nos lo había "
"dicho. E incluso después de todo este lío... Nos vamos sin más. No sé, "
"parece que todo haya sido en vano."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/cutscene/outro_02"
msgid ""
"But we stopped them, didn’t we? Maybe some lads from other battalions will "
"be thankful for that."
msgstr ""
"Pero los detuvimos, ¿no es así? Quizás algunos muchachos de otros batallones "
"os lo agradezcan."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/cutscene/outro_03"
msgid ""
"We’ve been through bloody hell, mate. And that’s just today. Why the hell "
"did Jerry even invade Belgium? They could’ve kept sitting on their asses "
"and… not start this whole thing…"
msgstr ""
"Hemos pasado por un auténtico infierno, amigo. Y eso solo hoy. ¿Por qué "
"demonios invadió Jerry Bélgica? Podrían haberse quedado sentados sin hacer "
"nada y... no haber empezado todo esto..."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/cutscene/outro_04"
msgid ""
"Well, I’ve heard the Russians are helping Jerry with fuel and industrial "
"crap. Maybe that’ll push Winnie to strike a deal with Jerry and we’ll be "
"home sooner than we think."
msgstr ""
"Bueno, he oído que los rusos están ayudando a Jerry con combustible y "
"porquerías industriales. Quizás eso empuje a Winnie a llegar a un acuerdo "
"con Jerry y podamos volver a casa antes de lo que pensamos."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/cutscene/outro_05"
msgid "You heard where we’re heading next?"
msgstr "¿Has oído adónde nos dirigimos ahora?"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/cutscene/outro_06"
msgid ""
"Some place in… Ehm, I don’t recall it, these French names are "
"unpronounceable. Don’t think it even matters, let’s just make it ‘till the "
"end."
msgstr ""
"En algún lugar de... Eh, no lo recuerdo, estos nombres franceses son "
"impronunciables. No creo que importe, sigamos hasta el final."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/cutscene/outro_07"
msgid "Mike… What if we don’t?"
msgstr "Mike... ¿Y si no lo hacemos?"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/cutscene/outro_08"
msgid ""
"You know… If Kenya taught me one thing, it’s how to enjoy the moment. Even "
"if you’re stuck in a bloody, smelly, godforsaken quagmire. We’re fine for "
"now. So shut up and enjoy the bloody view, Stuey."
msgstr ""
"Sabes... Si Kenia me ha enseñado algo, es a disfrutar del momento. Incluso "
"si estás atrapado en un lodazal sangriento, maloliente y abandonado por "
"Dios. Por ahora estamos bien. Así que cállate y disfruta de las malditas "
"vistas, Stuey."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/secret_bunker_01"
msgid "Oi, what’s the deal with these ancient things?"
msgstr "Oye, ¿qué pasa con estas cosas antiguas?"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/secret_bunker_02"
msgid ""
"These bunkers were built in the 30s. I don’t think they’re really useful. "
"Maybe it's worth looking around to find some ancient stuff though."
msgstr ""
"Estos búnkeres se construyeron en los años 30. No creo que sean realmente "
"útiles. Aunque quizá merezca la pena echar un vistazo para encontrar alguna "
"cosa antigua."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/secret_bunker_03"
msgid ""
"You’re really one of a kind, huh? I’m not a doctor but throwing grenades "
"when you’re in a bunker is not the smartest idea."
msgstr ""
"Eres único en tu especie, ¿eh? No soy médico, pero lanzar granadas cuando "
"estás en un búnker no es la idea más inteligente."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/attack_left_01"
msgid "The Germans are attacking our left flank!"
msgstr "¡Los alemanes están atacando vuestro flanco izquierdo!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/attack_left_02"
msgid "Another attack, left flank!"
msgstr "¡Otro ataque, flanco izquierdo!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/attack_left_03"
msgid "More Boche are coming from the left!"
msgstr "¡Vienen más boches por la izquierda!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/attack_mid_01"
msgid "Germans are trying to break through our central positions!"
msgstr "¡Los alemanes están intentando romper nuestras posiciones centrales!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/attack_mid_02"
msgid "More Germans advancing towards our central positions!"
msgstr "¡Más alemanes avanzando hacia nuestras posiciones centrales!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/attack_mid_03"
msgid "Central positions, another German attack!"
msgstr "¡Posiciones centrales, otro ataque alemán!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/attack_right_01"
msgid "German forces are attacking our right flank!"
msgstr "¡Las fuerzas alemanas están atacando vuestro flanco derecho!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/attack_right_02"
msgid "Watch out, Germans coming from the right!"
msgstr "¡Cuidado, vienen los alemanes por la derecha!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/narrator/attack_right_03"
msgid "Another attack on the right flank!"
msgstr "¡Otro ataque por el flanco derecho!"

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/tasks/01_evac"
msgid "Search for survivors and help to evacuate them"
msgstr "Buscar supervivientes y ayudar a evacuarlos."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/tasks/02_medics"
msgid "Protect the medical team. At least 1 medic must survive"
msgstr "Proteger al equipo médico. Al menos un médico debe sobrevivir."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/tasks/03_defense"
msgid "Hold your defensive positions on Dyle Line"
msgstr "Mantén tus posiciones defensivas en la línea Dyle."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/tasks/04_recapture"
msgid "Assist the allied forces to re-capture the northern position"
msgstr "Ayudar a las fuerzas aliadas a recuperar la posición norte."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/tasks/05_doc_allround"
msgid "<c(B29557)>[All-Round Doctrine]</c> Eliminate enemy howitzers"
msgstr "<c(B29557)>[Doctrina integral]</c> Eliminar los obuses enemigos."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/tasks/05_doc_defensive"
msgid "<c(B29557)>[Defensive Doctrine]</c> Eliminate enemy aircraft"
msgstr "<c(B29557)>[Doctrina defensiva]</c> Eliminar los aviones enemigos."

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1940_05_13_dyle/tasks/05_doc_irregular"
msgid ""
"<c(B29557)>[Irregular Doctrine]</c> Eliminate enemy emplacements by calling "
"artillery support"
msgstr ""
"<c(B29557)>[Doctrina irregular]</c> Elimina las posiciones enemigas "
"solicitando apoyo de artillería."

